t Vert.x JsonObject might need it. Curious whether vertx-core has jackson-databind, as the dependency tree shows only jackson-core. In Vert.x 5, maybe it won't be needed at runtime. I need to decide if an extra Maven dependency for io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 is necessary for OAuth2 tests. Running tests against existing JVM/native setups and local verification could be skipped. I'll think about running `./gradlew javaTest`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test setup risks**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether the native setup might be costly and if running Java tests ensures failures that aren't necessary. I really need to check if system properties are set up correctly for generation. With a library version of 5.0.0, it seems like the environment properties won't apply for version 5.0.1 unless specified in the builds. There’s definitely an issue with covering new scaffolds unless there’s guidance. I think I should use an advisory for actions because of agent guidance and avoid mentioning optional OAuth2 unless it's explicitly added since it could lead to unnecessary risks.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 is usable with its normal transitive dependencies and localhost Vert.x servers, but its Vert.x 5.0.1 stack resolves Netty 4.2.2.Final, so Java 25 native-image runtime tests likely need the same Netty unsafe-access system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set native test runtime system properties for the generated tests: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 for WebClient coverage; no external service or Docker container is needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The unsafe-access properties are driven by the Netty 4.2.x dependency and Java 25 native-image behavior; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\",\n    \"Avoid optional OAuth2-specific WebClient scenarios unless an additional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 test dependency is intentionally added.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08d27415b7b59478016a3f6e3c7790819687c85a61e22fab83\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1320, "output": 767, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27175, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782541873105, "responseId": "resp_08d27415b7b59478016a3f6e319ec881968e447531910190c4"}}
